When Amida was still in the unenlightened stage. He made a vow, that, on
becoming a Buddha. He would come and welcome to His Paradise all who heard
of His name and called upon it. . . , saying that if they would but turn
their minds to Him and call much upon Him. He would remake them, just as if
he were turning tiles and pebbles into gold.
